The game has changed. I feel it in the versions. I see it in the shitposts. I smell it in the games.
Much that once was, is lost. For few that now play who remember.
It all began with the forging of the Great Memes.
Three were given to Arteezy; youngest and cockiest of all memers.
Seven, to iceiceice, great offlaner and trollsman of the chinese halls.
And nine, nine memes were gifted to the bulldog, who above all else desired sheever.
For within these memes was bound the dank and the jokes to govern over each stream. But they were all of them deceived, for another meme was made. In the team of C9, in the flames of Tucker Fucker, the Dank Lord SingSing forged in secret, a master meme, to control all others. And into this meme he poured all his cruelty, his hairstyle and his will to draw all cocks.
One meme to rule them all.
One by one, the free peoples of DotA2 fell to the power of the meme. But there were some who resisted. A last alliance of men and grills marched against the armies of SingSing, and on the very slopes of TI, they fought for the freedom of DotA. Victory was near, but the power of the meme could not be undone. It was in this moment, when all hope had faded, that EternalEnvy, Team Leader of C9, kicked out SingSing from the team. And SingSing, enemy of the free peoples of DotA, was defeated.
The meme passed on to twitch chat, who had this one chance to destroy evil forever, but the dank memes are easily copypasta'd. And the meme of power has a will of its own.
It betrayed twitch, to its lag. And some things that should not have been forgotten were lost. History became legend. Legend became lore. And for two and a half thousand starladder seasons, the meme passed out of all knowledge.
Until, when chance came, it ensnared a new bearer. The meme came to the creature Mynuts, who took it deep into the tunnels under the Alliance Banner, and there it consumed him. The meme gave to Mynuts unnaturally dank name. For five hundred roaster changes it poisoned his games; and in the gloom of Mynuts's team, it waited.
Dankness crept back into the games of the dota. Rumor grew of a comic book in the East, whispers of a nameless team, and the Meme of Power perceived. Its time had now come. It abandoned Mynuts. But then something happened that the meme did not intend. It was picked up by the most unlikely team possible, compLexity of NA. For the time will soon come, where compLexity will shape the fortune of all...
